author: {'steamid': '76561198202046408', 'num_games_owned': 422, 'num_reviews': 329, 'playtime_forever': 22, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 22, 'last_played': 1476927904}
review:
Una de las características más destacadas de Strike.is: The Game es su sistema de personalización. Puedes adaptar tu personaje y tus armas para adaptarse a tu estilo de juego específico. Desde armas cuerpo a cuerpo hasta rifles de francotirador, cada opción tiene sus ventajas y desventajas, lo que te permite crear estrategias únicas para cada enfrentamiento.

La cooperación y la estrategia son esenciales en este mundo virtual. Puedes formar equipos con otros jugadores para coordinar ataques y defender posiciones clave, lo que añade una capa adicional de profundidad táctica al juego. La comunicación y la coordinación con tu equipo son esenciales para lograr la victoria en los enfrentamientos frenéticos.

Además de las batallas emocionantes, Strike.is: The Game también ofrece un aspecto social muy atractivo. Puedes hacer amigos, unirte a clanes y participar en eventos especiales con la comunidad del juego. La interacción con otros jugadores no solo enriquece la experiencia, sino que también crea una sensación de comunidad que te hace volver una y otra vez.

author: {'steamid': '76561198210919148', 'num_games_owned': 164, 'num_reviews': 36, 'playtime_forever': 21, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20, 'last_played': 1674316136}
review:
If Counter-Strike and Diep.io had a child but punched the fucking fetus, this would be it.
What the fuck, is this game supposed to be?
I mean, I like that it has a lot of content, there's many weapons, and there's many game modes.
But, after having tried all of those game modes, guess how many players I found?
ONE. One singular player.
On top of that, the game is laggy as fuck in terms of ping.
And the controls feel clunky in my opinion.
Maybe this game was fun when it wasn't dead, but it appears to me like it's a rip off of Diep.io
Waste of space, don't even bother installing this.

author: {'steamid': '76561198030784015', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 11208, 'playtime_forever': 16, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 16, 'last_played': 1618588359}
review:
Strike.is The Game is a mobile/browser game that got dumped on Steam, for no apparent reason apart from to reduce the average quality of games on Steam. 

Gameplay is PvP only.  You control a 2D retro pixel gun surrounded by a flat circle. 

It's actually more entertaining trying to imagine who thought this would be a fun idea for a game than actually playing this browser garbage.  People are aware 3D graphics exist, right?  You can play TF2 and dozens of other excellent FPS PvP games for free...

author: {'steamid': '76561198288058950', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2721, 'playtime_forever': 17, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 12, 'last_played': 1692632418}
review:
Ця гра - просто клас! З першого погляду вражає графіка. Для міні-гри вона все-таки дуже приємна. І в меню є різні фішки, щоб поліпшити своєго "героя".

Серед переваг:
- Доступність (або F2P)
- Підтримка слабких комп'ютерів
- Різноманітні види зброї та перків
- Настроювання
- Гарний графічний дизайн
- Присутність мультиплеєра (за замовчуванням)

А тепер до недоліків:
- Занадто плавний рух (для топсайд шутерів це дуже заважає)
- Обмежена кількість зброї та апгрейдів для "героя"
- Зависання під час руху

Загалом, я знайшов стільки речей. Гра нормальна, але все ще трохи сиро. Це одна з гідних F2P ігор. Надіюся, вам сподобався мій огляд гри :D

Оцінка: 3/5 (строга, але справедлива)

author: {'steamid': '76561198330000617', 'num_games_owned': 110, 'num_reviews': 221, 'playtime_forever': 921, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 914, 'last_played': 1612610151}
review:
Salut !

Ferește-te ca de dracu x_x

Un joc mega simplu și cu o idee faină, dar prost pusă în aplicare.

POVESTE:

Ești o bulă ce trage în alte bule.

GAMEPLAY:

Extrem de prost făcut, te miști greoi și îi mega ciudat de controlat.

OPTIMIZARE:

Merge bine, evident.

GRAFICĂ:

Plăcută.

DETALII:

Nu are glitch-uri sau bug-uri.

CONȚINUT:

Are ceva. Te poate distra vreo 25 de ore, pentru un joc moca, îi foarte bine.

a) Dacă vrei strict să te joci, te plictisești de el după 2-3 ore, după ce parcurgi toate modurile și te saturi de controlărul oribil.
b) Dacă colectezi trofee și skinuri, stai ceva vreme, 25 de ore cel puțin.

MULTIPLAYER:

Total mort.

CONCLUZIE:

Caută altceva, îi un faile total.

5/10

𝑷 𝒂 𝒄 𝒆

author: {'steamid': '76561198171846557', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 317, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 317, 'last_played': 1489887290}
review:
Again, this game is another ripoff of a game from the IO series (the games for your browser, and yes, I said the "IO series"), being the game this time Diep.io, by the same creators of Agar.io and Slither.io. 

So, I don't know, honestly, it's a little shooter game. It's fun, don't get me wrong, but there's one fatal flaw: You can't set your own controls. The controls at default are WASD or you used your arrows. I understand, it's been the control scheme for decades, but for touchtypers like me and some other people, we would like to set our own controls.

The real reason why it's a fatal flaw is because some people aren't familiar with this control scheme, and new people to these controls will not get used to it very quickly. This in turn makes people lose a lot more, hence the choppy controls.

Besides that, there's the re-usage of the music from the other games (Mitos.is and Worm.is), which was kind of a bad thing to do since there is no more variety. They could have at least enabled (for all games) to input your OWN music. That would have been very nice and I guaruntee that the games would get more players.

That's really about it, considering the game is very fluid compared to Diep.io. I have mixed feelings about this one, so in total, [i]5/10[/i].

author: {'steamid': '76561198362706693', 'num_games_owned': 58, 'num_reviews': 13, 'playtime_forever': 354, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 353, 'last_played': 1574742863}
review:
Awesome Game! Fun to play! although this game is terrible at currency, it took 2 days to get my first bought item. honestly, this company needs to ACTUALLY IMPROVE! by making it easier to get coins and lowering the prices if you dont make it easier, its boring without cool stuff, even in TF2 its easier to get items! let us actually play for the money! NOT WAIT FOR IT! and its not live either! ie: money = 50, goes back into game and picks up another coin, money still = 50. WHAT?! this is not how games work!!! the reason im recommending this is because of how fun it is. but still. this game's currency system is about 150-250 coins per day. 5 - 25 coins per hour! ugh, i would play this constantly if it had a better currency system. overall - gameplay = awesome | maps = cool | music = could use some work | currency = crap | gamemodes = eh.
there you go, my review for Strike.Is (mostly complains about currency.)

review:
I'd like to point out that in addition to the bad controls, the game rips off a number of features from a new Class-Based Multiplayer game which shall not be named. Each weapon gives you attributes that essentially make you your own class. For example:

[list]
[*] A short-range plasma rifle which lets you 'Blink' forward every few seconds
[*] A rifle that gives you the abilities 'Run' and [b]'Biotic Field Generator' [/b]
[*] A double-barreled shotgun that gives you a 'Healing Potion' which recharges every 12 seconds
[*] Long-range dual pistols with an ability to run and shoot 6 bullets rapidly
[*] A laser gun that gives you the ability to place a 'Magnetic Shield' around yourself
[*] A grenade launcher with the abilities 'Remote Detonate' and 'Frag Jump'
[*] A sniper rifle allowing 'Sniper Sight'
[*] A crossbow that shoots arrows but also has a 'Bouncing Shot' ability
[*]
[/list]

review: It was a good games. WAS is the key word there. When the simplicity of only having 5 different weapons IN THE ENTIRE GAME, and the game just GIVING you money, it was fun. More weapons is good, but character customizability is not. Remove customization, and the shitty controls. The old controls: WASD to move. Aim is separate. New Controls: W to go forward, S to go backward, AD to go left and right. HOW you wen forward depended on the aim. I HATE the controls now. Make an update that allows the new controls and the old controls, at least. And take away all of the utfits. It was trying too hard to be TF2. 2 Months Ago - 9/10. Now - 5/10.

review:
this is just another game trying to cash in on the craze Agar.io started. it feels that the name alone can entice players into playing it. Won't lie, it's somewhat enjoyable sometimes, but regardless the lack of love put into this game on the dev side shows.

If you like it, great. to me, and probably to many others, it's mediocre at best, tedius and dare I say one sided at worst. the characters are far too slow to allow any true feeling of action nor skill. TDM can become and stay very one-sided with the first team to pin down the other getting access to the best of the best weapons.

And, of course, boring AF, to me at least. Again, if you like it, great. I'm glad you can see something in this that I can't. This just, really is not for me.

"Strike.is? More lik ISIS, AMIRIGHT?" - XkewldudeX

author: {'steamid': '76561198235884198', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 740, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20, 'last_played': 1484859059}
review: On August 23 an update went out that basicly makes it simply load at the title screen forever, for pc users on windows 8.2 and even window ten; the new and best OS right? Reinstalling the game doesnt fix the problem. All the games made by the developers such as Mitos.is- Strike.is and Snake will not load. Simply at this point the IOS users are quite enjoying the games alone. Which is quite weird or an eye opener that a competive update came out for "everyone"; but however IOS users are only able to compete. SO is it intentional or not? Multiple users for pc are having a problem; while others can compete with a clean slate or at the least with out the competion of cross platform users- Pc. If you on any platform support the games by this developer, you need to look at how and why a competive update came out while stopping the amount of possible players from competing; in logic terms it's simple they needed to unoffically clear some of the players out the way. Some might say "no way they'd be able to do that"; well ask yourself first do you think they will restart it after they fix the problems? "NO way; they cant strip the winnings from the player(s) that did win", even if the devs toke half the playing field away. Good luck to the ones still playing that will enjoy less players. It really doesnt take alot to see that the timing is the key to this lock out of player. It even calls it an update opening more compation to the game with a new season. They are inadvertinly stating that it is a hand over to IOS users to feel grand about the support they are due. DO NOT support this action or the future actions like this. Simply they know what they did and it will happen surely to the communtiy again when season 10 comes. Donations would be asked by the devs to fix these simple "scandals tactics"; which in its self is one correct? Do not recommend to friends and people you like in the real world, you'd only be giving them a shot in the back.

review:
I stumbled across this little game last night while playing Mitos.is. I found it quite enjoyable. Lots of the reviewers are but hurt because they say it is a rip off of some other games, because you know that has never happened before.. dota, league of legends, heroes of newerth, smite, heroes of the storm... it happens all the time get over it.

pros
- fun times
- lots of killing
- variety of guns
- purchaseable starting equipment
- various game modes, Capture the flag, Team Fortress, Death match, and others.

con
- need to remap the W key from moving the direction the mouse is to just UP.
- minor bugs
- needs more maps for game modes

author: {'steamid': '76561198063489127', 'num_games_owned': 2158, 'num_reviews': 380, 'playtime_forever': 249, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 249, 'last_played': 1471688896}
review:
Genres:
~ Online-Mehrspieler, Free-To-Play, 2D, Top-Down-Shooter

Positiv:
+ Gilden
+ Spieler-Skins
+ 7 Modi, auch Ranglisten-Modi vorhanden
+ guter Soundtrack
+ "tägliche Aufgaben"
+ spielinterne Errungenschaften mit Belohnungen
+ 10 Waffen mit unterschiedlichen Fähigkeiten
+ Schutzzeit nach Spawn, in der man keinen Schaden nimmt
+ „Privater Raum“/benutzerdefinierter Raum mit In-Game-Währung erstellbar
+ einfache Steuerung

Ansichtssache:
+- schlichte Grafik
+- simpel, wenig fordernd

Negativ:
- unzerstörbare Umgebung
- dauerhaft kleine Vorteile durch Echtgeldeinsatz
- teilweise in Englisch
- unendlich Munition und teilweise schlecht durchdachte Karten/Level, wodurch dauerhaftes Festsetzen der Gegner einfach wird, sodass die Gegner keine Chance haben
- unangekündigtes Zurücksetzen der eigenen Statistiken kann nach Update passieren
- nur im Modus "Deathmatch" Erfahrung nach Levelhöhe des Gegners, wodurch man viel mehr Erfahrung als in anderen Modi erhält, sodass Motivation für andere Modi nicht gegeben ist

Anmerkung:
* keine Sprachausgabe

author: {'steamid': '76561198074048831', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 347, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 275, 'last_played': 1515027389}
review:
I read a lot of crazy bad reviews for this game...and unless you are a graphics whore...there is no reason not to love this game...oh I guess maybe it doesnt have zombies either...but lets face it, that whole zombie theme is started to get old.

This is a super solid casual shooter.
It has fast paced action.
It has super smooth controls,
It has guns that make you teleport.
It has retroish top down graphics...the graphics are not its stong point, but they are effective.

author: {'steamid': '76561198115407298', 'num_games_owned': 952, 'num_reviews': 455, 'playtime_forever': 5, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5, 'last_played': 1469967170}
review:
7 мая я написал обзор на  Worm.is «Чего нахрен только нет в стиме. Браузерные игры уже бл"ть качаем.» и блять через пару месяцев, а если быть точным то 15 июля появляется такая хуета как strike.is хаха боже да как тут блять еще один гомункул agario появился (или кого он там блять) Мало того что она скажем так пингует (не пишите что это не так у 36% игроков именно так и похуй какой инет ). Наверно самые лучшие программисты создали эту «оригинальную» игру. Давайте  же почитаем положительные обзоры, но кажется половина обзор выглядеть так «ана прикаленая бизканичность из бизконичнасте  » или «тпасеночсгн6кычп прсрпваенарпаамна» можете даже сами убедиться в этом. Ну вот нашел вроде годный(хаха) положительный обзор смотрим + этой игры «1. У нас не какие-то там пукалки, а реальное оружие, типа снайперская винтовка, пулемёт и т.д.» Хахаха реальное оружие стреляет охуенными красными шариками, а физика у них там вообще заебись. «2. Каждое оружие имеет свою особенность, например с пистолетом ты можешь ускоряться, а с плазмо-пушкой - телепортироваться» ахуеть теперь можно и нахуя здесь это надо?. «3.Скины и их синхронизация с вашим аккаунтом» ахуеть инновация прям. «5.Оружие и патроны надо подбирать» РЕАЛИЗМ ХУЛИ ВОТ ЭТО + за это лайк нахуй. Ну а другие + это уже совсем пиздец на подобие ( Игра БЕСПЛАТНАЯ ) 
(Пришлось играть аж 5 минут что бы написать обзор)
Ладно всем спасибо за то что уделили внимание(да и сорян за агрессию) и удачки.
И нахуй эту политику стим когда такое дерьмо проходит в наш любимый каталог игр.

author: {'steamid': '76561198187037415', 'num_games_owned': 139, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 252, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 195, 'last_played': 1470627339}
review:
Игрушка класс. Первое что бросается в глаза это графика. Для мини-игры  она все-таки приятная. Есть меню и прочие плюшки для улучшения "перса".
Плюсы:
- Доступность (или F2P)
- Поддержка слабых компов
- Различные виды оружий и перки
- Кастомизация
- Хороший графон
-Наличие мультиплеера (по default'y)
А теперь минусы:
- Слишком плавное движение (для топсайд шутеров это очень мешает)
- Мало оружий и апгрейдов для "перса"
- Подвисания во время движения
Впринципе столько я нашел. Игрушка нормас, но еще сыровато немного. Это одна из годных F2P 
Надеюсь вам понравился обзор на игрушку :D
3.5/5 (строгая оценка)

author: {'steamid': '76561198088234503', 'num_games_owned': 158, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 13, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 13, 'last_played': 1469634633}
review:
Also ich schließe mich da meinem englisch-sprachigen Vorredner an:

Falls ihr bereits Titel wie agar.io gezockt habt und sie auch auch nur annähernd gefallen solltet ihr diesen Spaß definitiv ausprobieren. Es ist eigentlich auch genauso aufgebaut wie agar.io, bloß besitzt ihr Waffen .. das Ziel ist so viele Gegner wie möglich auszuschalten. 

Ihr könnt eure Waffen wechseln, Pistole, zwei Pistolen, Maschinengewehr, Sturmgewehr, Schrotflinte oder Scharfschützengewehr .. ihr habt einiges zur Auswahl.

Die paar MB lohnt es sich wenigstens mal reinzugucken, die zahlreichen negativen Bewertungen stammen wohl von wirklich von Usern die sich unter dem Titel ein riesen Spiel mit massen an Kontent und jahrelangem Spielspaß vorgestellt haben .. obwohl ein Einschätzen beim ersten Blick auf die Bilder oben nicht allzu schwer sein sollte.

review:
Olha, eu só joguei 1 hora e alguns minutos e o que eu vou dizer eu tenho certeza:
A Freakinware não está sendo original, mas, o que isso importa para nós, jogadores? São eles que tem que fazer os jogos. E não, esse jogo não é uma cópia do Diep.io, por que a jogabilidade, interface (que é igual a todos os jogos da empresa), sistema de níveis, armas. Mas não podemos dizer que esse jogo surgiria mesmo que Diep.io não fosse lançado. A ideia é a mesma, mas o que foi feito é diferente. Se não está feliz vá jogar Diep.io. E se quiser ser mais feliz, jogue os dois :DDD

O jogo é bom pra passar o tempo :D

review:
Many People think this game is a Complete Ripoff of Diep.io. It actually is quite diffrent from Diep.io.

I would recomend you to atleast try this out for yourself, as its a free game and its quite fun.

You Play as a Cell with a gun? (Idk why but whatever) and you go around shotting people and collecting better guns and using diffrent abilitys that come with the guns (Ie. the laser rifle allows teleporting, smaller guns allow Sprinting, And bigger guns allowyou to scopeand get high damage shots).

This game is its own game and it is quite addicting and fun to play.

review:
Metade da diversão de Diep.io 

Cons: 
- Requer login no site do desenvolvedor pra ter acesso a todas as armas e equipamentos atraves da compra de coins
- A interface é a mesma dos jogos moveis, incluindo botoes virtuais.
- Mapa pequeno demais, faz a morte ser uma certeza.
- Poucos servidores e pouco frequentados 

Pros:
- possivelmente vai ser atualizado e aprimorado

Half the fun of Diep.io

Cons:
- Requires login on the developer's site to have access to all weapons and equipment through the purchase of coins
- The interface is the same as mobile games, including virtual buttons.
- Too small map, makes death a certainty.
- Fewer servers and underpopulated

Pros:
- Will possibly be upgraded and enhanced

author: {'steamid': '76561198083944846', 'num_games_owned': 387, 'num_reviews': 28, 'playtime_forever': 6, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6, 'last_played': 1469098645}
review:
This obviously started as a tried-and-true-formula sort of thing. It's becoming quite the theme for them to take games about bubbles and cells from websites, steal the whole damn thing, add microtransactions, remove the joy, and rebrand it as their own. Mitos.is = Agar.io, Worm.is = Slither.io, Strike.is = Diep.io. It [i]started[/i] that way. But it seems the developers had a change of heart. They didn't want to have it be a complete clone of diep.io. What would be the point? So they removed the leveling system, removed the tree system, removed smooth movement, removed the absence of lag (my little joke, all their games lag to shit), and added walls and barriers. It's a god-awful game. The other ones were good games, if judged on their own (for the sole reason that the developers straight-up ripped off even better games). This one isn't. 8 directional movement, lag like you wouldn't believe, and [i]barriers[/i], which have no place in a cell game. None. 

Oh, and for bonus ducks, they stole Overwatch's loading animation. [u]What.[/u]

author: {'steamid': '76561198133966921', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 10, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 10, 'last_played': 1468927702}
review:
Sinceramente, este juego es el mejor juego, si quieres desesperarte por sus ingentes cantidades de LAG, no tiene mala pinta y los juegos de estos creadores no suelen estar mal, Mitos.is estaba bastante bien, pero bueno, mis notas son:

Planteamiento: Divertido, algunas armas y parece que tiene desbloqueables 6,5/10

Forma de juego: Tiene varios modos de juego multijugador, variados y algo "innovadores" 7/10

Precio: GRATIS 10/10

Actualizaciones: Parece que se han comprometido en parte para mejorar este juego 7.5/10

Hub y respawn: no me gusta nada, no puedes elegir server ni nada, te coloca automaticamente 4.5/10

NOTA FINAL: 6.3 (obviamente no sumo la puntuación del precio).

review:
Disclaimer: Me, like many, MANY others, downloaded this game to write a Review.

Disclaimer 2: If you're reading this review about a game that you THINK you might be interested in, and is Offended by this review, Please know that my intent was not to do this. I Apologize if this is the Case, but please, i Insist you read on why this game is a Pile of Wank.

TL;DR: Don't download anything from Freakinware. They're Copycat F*cknuggets riding on the Hype train that are Agar.io, Slither.io, and Diep.io.

[h1]What is this Game?[/h1]

This "[i]game[/i]" is Strike.is, made by Freakinware Studios.

Or Freakinware Limited. Fitting, as their Game Developing Career is indeed, [i]Limited[/i].

[h1]Did they make anything Unique?[/h1]

Let me answer that as simply as possible.

[b]F*CK NO![/b]

Freakinware also made games like "Mitos.is" and "Worm.is" Both [b]CLEAR COPIES[/b] of the Hit browser games such as Agar.io and Slither.io.

Let me give you the Rundown of the games "made" by Freakinware.

[list]
   [*] Mitos.is = [url=Agar.io]Agar.io[/url]
   [*] Worm.is = [url=Slither.io]Slither.io[/url]
   [*] Strike.is = [url=Diep.io]Diep.io[/url]
[/list]
(All are Browser games. Please, play those instead of this.)

Every game they claim to be original are DAMN NEAR FACIMILES. (Facimile, an exact copy.)
The only f*cking Difference with these games are Pets, Microtransactions, and Free-use Dubstep.

To think these [strike]C*nts[/strike] are making [b]MONEY[/b] off these piles of Wank [b]BAFFLES ME![/b]

[h1]What about the Game itself? What's the Gameplay like?[/h1]

Honestly, I couldn't tell you. Like i said in the Disclaimer, i simply Downloaded this game to insult the people that Published it. I Recommend you read the reviews of people who TRIED to play this.

[h1]How can you be sure Diep.io didn't copy Strike.is?[/h1]

Because i PERSONALLY PLAYED Diep.io BEFORE this got on Steam, BEFORE Popular Youtubers (Such as Markiplier, Jacksepticeye, ETC.) played Diep.io. After that, POOF, Strike.is appeared on Greenlight.

Can't wait for Hatfilms to say this is Better that Diep.io... Ugh.

[h1]Why are you making this Review?[/h1]

It [i][b]sucks[/b][/i] when your ideas get stolen. When your stolen ideas earn [i]money for the thiefs,[/i] That's just worse.

[h1]The Conclusion[/h1]

This game doesn't DESERVE an Out-of-10 rating.

Go play Diep.io instead.

author: {'steamid': '76561197966738565', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 35, 'playtime_forever': 39, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 39, 'last_played': 1470222308}
review:
[b]AGGIORNAMENTO[/b] con l'uscita dell'ultima patch i controlli sono sensibilmente peggiorati rendendo il gioco molto più frustrante rispetto a prima. In queste condizioni il mio voto passa da positivo a NEGATIVO, sperando di poter tornare sui miei passi quando questi problemi saranno risolti.

Non capisco la maggior parte delle recensioni di questo gioco, sembrano tutte scritte da ♥♦♣♠. Devono averci giocato un minuto, non sono riusciti a fare una streak di uccisioni e allora hanno deciso che il gioco faceva schifo e andava affossato con giudizi negativi. 

Strike.is: è un gioco semplice e immediato, i pulsanti da usare sono i soliti: WASD per muoversi, F per scambiare arma e il mouse per puntare e sparare (modalità standard e speciale).
Modalità di base e azione immediata, pochi fronzoli.

Unico aspetto negativo, occorre registrarsi per personalizzare il personaggio e acquistare potenziamenti e altro - cosa NON scritta nella pagina del gioco su Steam.

review: Strike.is was alright. its not the worst game I have played by far. The game pretty much functions like Mitos.is but instead of eating other cells you shoot them with gun pickups found around the map. each gun has a special ability like sprinting, zooming, rapid fire, etc.  I would only recommend the game if you already liked of Mitos.is or Slither.io and even then I would advise you to never spend any money on any of the above games.

author: {'steamid': '76561198059971262', 'num_games_owned': 2465, 'num_reviews': 632, 'playtime_forever': 5, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5, 'last_played': 1468555327}
review:
After making a rip-off of agar.io with Mitos.is, and copying slither.io with worm.is, this time it's diep.io with strike.is!

It may also be a rip-off of Vertix.io, but it seems more like diep.io, those two are quite similar. One has level up and stats, the other, classes. 

The only differences between Strike.is and Diep.io / Vertix.io ? Ugly graphics, full of microtransactions. 

I wonder which .io game they will copy next, I'm on the edge of my seat!

This game also contain their two other games; it's basically the same launcher with three store pages.
